28/07/2003
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Police announced on Sunday (27 July) that they have arrested a man for illegal possession of about 2,000 valuable artifacts dating from the Stone Age to the time of the Ottoman Empire. 
The hoard reportedly includes 1,260 silver and gold coins, 747 artifacts, 37 stone tools, 35 rings and a marble bas relief. 
The man, whose identity was not revealed, allegedly dug up some of the artifacts himself and purchased others on the black market. 
(AFP - 27/07/03)
